v1.0.0
* Complete experimental design and inference framework for two-arm sequential (one-by-one) and fixed designs
* Sequential one-by-one designs: Bernoulli, BCRD, Efron Biased Coin, Atkinson Covariate-Adjusted Biased Coin, KK14/KK21/KK21stepwise Matching on the Fly, Pocock-Simon, SPBR, iBCRD, Urn, Random Block Size
* Fixed designs: CRD, blocking, A-optimal, D-optimal
* Unified R6 inference hierarchy supporting continuous, count, incidence, ordinal, proportion, and survival response types
* Inference methods: OLS/GLS, robust regression, quantile regression, Wilcoxon, GLMs (logistic, Poisson, negative binomial, beta, ordinal), GEE, GLMM, Cox PH, Weibull, Clayton copula, LWA Cox, stratified Cox, RMST, log-rank, Gehan rank, g-computation, modified Poisson, Newcombe/Miettinen-Nurminen risk differences, log-binomial, binomial identity-link, zero/one-inflated beta, hurdle models, zero-inflated models, partial proportional odds, ridit, paired sign test, Jonckheere-Terpstra
* KK designs support dual-strategy pooling: IVWC (inverse-variance weighted combination) and Combined Likelihood
* Zhang (2026) exact test-inversion randomization CI for incidence outcomes
* Randomization and bootstrap confidence intervals with parallel bisection
* High-performance C++ solvers (IRLS, L-BFGS, OpenMP) for bootstrap and randomization inference
* Missing data imputation via missRanger and missForest
* Support for unequal allocation, censored survival, and custom randomization statistics
